<paragraph blockId="1.[264,432,483,509]" box="[264,432,483,509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
<heading bold="true" box="[264,432,483,509]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" reason="1">
<taxonomicName box="[264,432,483,509]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Acentropinae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,432,483,509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Acentropinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,559,705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Until recently 
<taxonomicName box="[438,596,559,585]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Acentropinae">Acentropinae</taxonomicName>
was known as Nymphulinae (
<collectionCode box="[964,1034,559,585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">ICZN</collectionCode>
<number box="[1044,1108,559,585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2003.0">2003</number>
). It is represented worldwide by more than 
<number box="[573,617,599,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="700.0">700</number>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Heppner" box="[731,905,599,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" refString="Heppner, J. B. (1991) Faunal regions and the diversity of Lepidoptera. Tropical Lepidoptera, 2, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="1991">
Heppner 
<number box="[845,905,599,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and in the Neotropical region by nearly 
<number box="[350,394,639,665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="250.0">250</number>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Munroe" box="[512,682,639,665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" refString="Munroe, E. G. (1995) Nymphulinae. pp. 48 - 51. In: Heppner, J. B. (Ed.), Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera, Volume 3. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera and Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, liv + 243 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Munroe 
<number box="[619,682,639,665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Galapagos Islands only one species of this subfamily has been detected.
</paragraph>
